                <div class="explanation">
                    <h3>Italy's Manufacturing Excellence</h3>
                    <p>Italy's economic structure reveals a particularly strong manufacturing sector that represents 23.8% of GDP, significantly above the EU average of 21.2%. This manufacturing strength positions Italy as the second-largest manufacturing economy in the EU after Germany, and reflects the country's deep industrial heritage and continued innovation in traditional sectors.</p>
                    
                    <p>The manufacturing sector's prominence explains much of Italy's global trade performance and economic resilience. Italian manufacturers excel in machinery production, automotive components, fashion and luxury goods, and food processingâ€”sectors that combine traditional craftsmanship with modern technology. This industrial base provides Italy with a competitive advantage in global markets and helps explain the country's significant trade surplus in manufactured goods.</p>
                </div>
